{"post":{"id":61,"user_id":"6","body":"Hello guys, 

angryBelieve me,  angry when I say this....  angry angry  angry

Grandlead heritage is a spin off of practical bullshtako (bullshit). Imagine them starting off with questions of technical knowledge, customer service, logistics and customer management, then you see people bowing thinking hard to find answers to those questions.

Pens up, Up next, video presentations of fashola and few entrepreneurs. As that was not enough...then a dude with a big attitude waltz in after being invited on stage. 

This gentleman started and few people stood up and waltz out like a boss they are. And so, the pep talk started, the gentleman made me remember all my experience with GNLD folks, wasting my tfare and time. 

I remained, smiled at the individual, then he started bragging about his qualifications and all. His sugar coated mouth began, explaining his backup plan, contingency plan and retirement plans. 

He said and I quote "I want to retire by age 30" having a landed property in ikorodu and begin tenancy.. I began to wonder how does this information help us discern the job specification. 

I was invited for graduate trainee position, and others were invited for other positions by different referrals. 

I left, then a friend on nairaland whom I met there prior to our communications and meet up plans in the previous day, told me they requested for money, which became clear that this individuals are looking for loyal, daft, jobfull people to feel their pockets for training kits and begin marketing jobs. 

So tell me isn't this GNLD!!!!!!!or what ever they discribe themselves as. 

So I drew my conclusion as tfare wasted, time wasted = non-fruitful endeavor = useless COY. Ignore their SMS or emails and search for other jobs. They even have a shitty website with no specificity as they also post jobs of other firms. 

#DECLINE EVERY INVITATION FROM GRANDLEAD HERITAGE as it isn't a legitimate job placement. 

Thank you for reading.

{"post":{"id":64,"user_id":"12","body":"This company has been associated with the extortion of funds from people. They claim to carry out several tests for which payment must be made. 
Also, no legitimate website has been found for this organization. 
beware people!


"Dear Intending Trainee,


With reference to your application about the Oil & Gas
Training/Employment Opportunity.
Currently, there is a new batch of lucrative oil jobs opportunities
available in the Petroleum Industry.

Based on the exploration contract to recruit new employees to undergo
a short training course that will enable trainees work in the Oil &
Gas Fields.
There will be a two stage progressive method to evaluate trainees,to
ensure that they fit into the Oilfield Training and Employment
Program.

There will be an online test on the 29th of September 2012,by 5pm
prompt.

All Intending trainees are expected to apply for,"A Petroleum e-book".
Application for this Petroleum e-book starts on the 24th of September
2012 and closes on the 28th of September 2012 for the issuance of
this Petroleum e-book.
Questions to be asked during the online test will come strictly
from this Petroleum e-book. All Intending trainees must obtain a
copy to enable intending trainees prepare for the online test on the
29th of September 2012.



However,the cost for the Petroleum e-book is N5,000. The Petroleum
e-book comes with a registration number and a copyright trademark.
Thus to place order for the Petroleum e-book,you are expected to make
deposit of the sum of N5,000, to our company's bank details below;


Account Name: Globaldrill Bay Oil & Gas Limited
Bank: Diamond Bank PLC
Account Number:0026913945


After payment,you should send Scan proof of payment to our email below.
We will then contact you immediately via email with your registration
details and your Petroleum e-book,so that you can download it and
print out for easy study.
It is very important that you obtain your Petroleum e-book on time to
enable you to start preparing for the online test that will hold
on the 29th of September 2012,by 5pm prompt.

The online test will be a qualifier to undertake the
Advance Oil Drilling Training that will lead to Employment
in the Oil & Gas industry.

The training course outline will cover areas such as;
*Introduction to Offshore Drilling
*BDC-Basic Drilling, Completion & Workover Operations
*EPB-Exploration and Production Process Basics
*Health, Safety & Environment

The above courses provides a technical overview of the phases,
operations, and terminology used in Exploration and Production
Process.

All applicants must be above 18 years of age and medically fit to
undergo the Oil & Gas Practical Training. The training is open to both
male & female trainees.

For Official inquiries,visiting days and hours to the company's
Lagos liaison office is on Monday's,Wednesday's and Friday's;
between the hours of 10am to 11am.


Signed,

Management

{"post":{"id":61,"user_id":"6","body":"Hello guys, 

angryBelieve me,  angry when I say this....  angry angry  angry

Grandlead heritage is a spin off of practical bullshtako (bullshit). Imagine them starting off with questions of technical knowledge, customer service, logistics and customer management, then you see people bowing thinking hard to find answers to those questions.

Pens up, Up next, video presentations of fashola and few entrepreneurs. As that was not enough...then a dude with a big attitude waltz in after being invited on stage. 

This gentleman started and few people stood up and waltz out like a boss they are. And so, the pep talk started, the gentleman made me remember all my experience with GNLD folks, wasting my tfare and time. 

I remained, smiled at the individual, then he started bragging about his qualifications and all. His sugar coated mouth began, explaining his backup plan, contingency plan and retirement plans. 

He said and I quote "I want to retire by age 30" having a landed property in ikorodu and begin tenancy.. I began to wonder how does this information help us discern the job specification. 

I was invited for graduate trainee position, and others were invited for other positions by different referrals. 

I left, then a friend on nairaland whom I met there prior to our communications and meet up plans in the previous day, told me they requested for money, which became clear that this individuals are looking for loyal, daft, jobfull people to feel their pockets for training kits and begin marketing jobs. 

So tell me isn't this GNLD!!!!!!!or what ever they discribe themselves as. 

So I drew my conclusion as tfare wasted, time wasted = non-fruitful endeavor = useless COY. Ignore their SMS or emails and search for other jobs. They even have a shitty website with no specificity as they also post jobs of other firms. 

#DECLINE EVERY INVITATION FROM GRANDLEAD HERITAGE as it isn't a legitimate job placement. 

Thank you for reading.

{"post":{"id":176,"user_id":"29","body":"Sequel to your application via our online advertorial ,after much evaluation of your profile on our portal,We were impressed with your qualifications and skills which makes you a prospective candidate, We are please to inform you that you have been selected and invited for an interview with our HR Director as an Administrative Officer.

BGI GROUP NIGERIA LIMITED is a fast-growing business strategy and human capacity development outfit dedicated to providing innovation business solution to her teeming clients and customers.



Location: 4 All Ogungbeye st, off Amara-olu,( first gate bus stop), Agidingbi, Ikeja

beware people!


"Dear Intending Trainee,

Gas Fields.

ensure that they fit into the Oilfield Training and Employment
Program.

There will be an online test on the 29th of September 2012,by 5pm
prompt.

All Intending trainees are expected to apply for,"A Petroleum e-book".
Application for this Petroleum e-book starts on the 24th of September
2012 and closes on the 28th of September 2012 for the issuance of
this Petroleum e-book.
Questions to be asked during the online test will come strictly
from this Petroleum e-book. All Intending trainees must obtain a
copy to enable intending trainees prepare for the online test on the
29th of September 2012.

e-book comes with a registration number and a copyright trademark.

deposit of the sum of N5,000, to our company's bank details below;


Account Name: Globaldrill Bay Oil & Gas Limited
Bank: Diamond Bank PLC
Account Number:0026913945


After payment,you should send Scan proof of payment to our email below.
We will then contact you immediately via email with your registration
details and your Petroleum e-book,so that you can download it and
print out for easy study.
It is very important that you obtain your Petroleum e-book on time to
enable you to start preparing for the online test that will hold
on the 29th of September 2012,by 5pm prompt.

The online test will be a qualifier to undertake the
Advance Oil Drilling Training that will lead to Employment
in the Oil & Gas industry.

The training course outline will cover areas such as;
*Introduction to Offshore Drilling
*BDC-Basic Drilling, Completion & Workover Operations
*EPB-Exploration and Production Process Basics
*Health, Safety & Environment

The above courses provides a technical overview of the phases,
operations, and terminology used in Exploration and Production
Process.

All applicants must be above 18 years of age and medically fit to
undergo the Oil & Gas Practical Training. The training is open to both
male & female trainees.

For Official inquiries,visiting days and hours to the company's
Lagos liaison office is on Monday's,Wednesday's and Friday's;
between the hours of 10am to 11am.

Greetings from Lagos.pls help me share cos I know most of your followers are here in Lagos. its God that
saved me yesterday.I applied for a job via Jiji on Monday, on Wednesday I was called for interview in Maryland Lagos.I got to Maryland took a bike to the location for the interview. I told them to give me a minute let me inform my pple that I won't be home early as I told them, l went towards the gate to call my sister, as I was answering the call two men came down making them four, they started shouting on me that I'm wasting their time that is like I'm not ready for the job.As this was happening a guy from no where came behind me all I heard was "my case is different "and I said so is mine.

He said he saw the winners bangle I was wearing that I should meet him outside the gate. I followed him, he asked what brought me here, I told him I came for an interview, he said I should thank my God that I saw him if not it will be a different story by evening.That I should leave the place immediately that the pple are using charms on pple. I thanked him and entered a bike that dropped one guy at the gate there and left. They called and called I no pick.This morning they sent a text that my interview has been rescheduled.Lets be vigilant with online Jobs I have not been myself since yesterday.)  You are SHORTLISTED for an assessment on THUR 27-04-17 by 10am at
